# SuperSpecs Active

Four phases, always in order: **Plan → Execute → Verify → Ship**

## Commands

| Phase | Command | What |
|---|---|---|
| 1.1 Plan | `/discuss` | Capture decisions before planning |
| 1.2 Plan | `/spec` | Write spec (requires DISCUSS.md) |
| 1.3 Plan | `/grill` | **Mandatory gate** — READY verdict required before execution |
| 2.1 Execute | `/pick-spec` | Validate + prepare execution |
| 2.2 Execute | `/branch` | Create branch/worktree |
| 2.3 Execute | `/subagent` | Parallel task dispatch |
| 2.4 Execute | `/tdd` | RED-GREEN-REFACTOR |
| 2.5 Execute | `/code-review` | Between tasks, critical blocks |
| 3 Verify | `/verify` | Full suite + scenario coverage, then wiki import |
| 4 Ship | `/ship` | PR + archive + next cycle |

## Hard Rules
1. No implementation code before a failing test
2. Critical code-review findings block all progress
3. Spec must fit a fresh 200k context window
4. `/grill` must reach READY verdict before `/pick-spec`
5. Every shipped feature gets a wiki page
